notesStmt.note: Folios 100-106 are fragments of appended pieces (much damaged).
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: A festival prayer book, according to the (old) French rite.

msItem.title: The order of hafṭarot for the whole year
Rules and special pieces for Ḥanukah and Ta῾aniyot

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1 2; ruled lines: 21; written lines: 20; Uniform layout. Visible pricking and hard-point ruling. Hair side and flesh side are distinguishable. Some marginal notes and additions.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Ashkenazi (French) square and semi-cursive script, punctuated, of the 13th century.

binding.p: Post-1600. Brown leather. Boxed. Spine: 'Machazor. German Rite. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional Or. 19,664.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Adolphus Asher: (b. 1800, d. 1853), Berlin bookseller and dealer to the British Museum (see 131-153: purchased from him on 12 November 1853: inscribed (folio [107v]).
